# API and data contract

- **Types**: Shared shapes (`ChatMessage`, `Source`, `ChatService`, `WidgetOptions`, etc.) live in **`src/types/index.ts`**. Extend the interface there before implementing; do not duplicate ad-hoc object types in components.
- **HTTP / backend**: Implement **`ChatService`** in **`src/services/`** (or a single dedicated module). **`App.tsx`** (or one thin wiring layer) imports the implementation—**do not** call `fetch` / `XMLHttpRequest` directly from presentational components.
- **Responses**: Map backend failures to **user-safe** messages; avoid leaking status text, stack traces, or internal IDs in the UI. The App layer renders the fixed Finnish safe string exported from **`src/errorCopy.ts`**; `ChatService` error `message` values are never forwarded to the DOM (they may only be logged to the dev console, gated on `import.meta.env.DEV`). See AC-42.
- **Mock swap**: Replacing the mock means a new service file that **implements the same `ChatService` contract** and updating the import in `App.tsx`—do not fork divergent method signatures without updating `src/types/index.ts` and call sites.
